scene.message:
Mark's Mom: Ma-kun! You came{nl}
at just the right time!{waitkey}{clearbox}Mommy's out shopping, but the{nl}
bags are heavy, so Ma-kun,{nl}
come along with me!{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Ohhh~...{wait_fr:53} So you're{nl}
this "Ma-kun," are you?{nl}
Eh, Masao Inaba...?{waitkey}{ret}

Mark's Mom: Ma-kun! You{nl}
mustn't call your mommy{nl}
an old hag!?{waitkey}{clearbox}And here I was thinking I'd{nl}
buy you a nice shirt or{nl}
something!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: "Ma-kun," huh...{nl}
Just as embarrassing a name{nl}
as "young master."{waitkey}{ret}

Mark's Mom: Oh, are these{nl}
your friends? But this shop{nl}
is pricey~ Hey Ma-kun, take{nl}
a little look!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: It's got nothing to do{nl}
with me! Hey, {ctl0f:1}!{nl}
We're leaving!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark's Mom: Honestly, that{nl}
boy...{wait_fr:32} Everyone, do be{nl}
good friends with my Ma-kun.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark's Mom: Oh my, Ma-kun!{nl}
You came back for me~? Why,{nl}
that's perfect timing~!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: You're hiding around{nl}
here, right? It's me, Masao.{nl}
I'm not a demon.{waitkey}It's okay, come on out. I'll{nl}
take you all the way home.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Ah, {ctl0f:1}, it's nothing.{nl}
I'm fine, fine.{waitkey}{clearbox}My old lady definitely went{nl}
home before anything could{nl}
happen to her.{waitkey}{clearbox}She's probably glued to some{nl}
tabloid show, making a fuss{nl}
right about now.{wait_fr:32} Let's go!{waitkey}{ret}
